description: Demolition of Rafferty House and Sentinel House and provision of new entrance to South Point. Erection of two buildings (one up to thirteen stories in height and one up to fourteen stories in height) comprising a mixed development of one hundred and twenty eight 1-bedroomed, one hundred and fifteen 2-bedroomed and eleven 3-bedroomed self contained flats (incorporating 61 units of affordable housing) and 902m2 of floorspace at ground floor level for purposes falling within Class A1 (Retail) or A3 (Restaurant and Caf) of the Town and Country Planning Use Classes Order 205 (as amended) together with a total of 192 car parking spaces, 3 car club spaces and 354 cycle spaces (including 118 car parking spaces, 7 motor cycle and 82 cycle spaces for the existing South Point Office building) at basement and ground floor levels, service yard, hard and soft landscaping, new access from Sutton Court Road and provision of future land level changes and pedestrian access to Sutton Station.
